summary:
The query involves recognizing helmet cells—also called schistocytes—as indicative of microangiopathic hemolytic anemias resulting from vascular damage and RBC fragmentation. While spherocytosis leads to rounded cells rather than helmet forms, hemolytic uremic syndrome (HUS) is associated with schistocytosis and thus correctly identifies the presence of these distinctive cellular findings among available options.

Final Answer: \boxed{\text{A}}  

Note: This summary reflects actual medical knowledge despite limited direct support in initial retrievals because the term “helmet cell” unambiguously denotes schistocytes linked to microvascular injury such as in HUS.

